learning_outcomes.en:
On completion of the course a student:
1) is aware of contemporary theories of literature, fiction elements, poetry and drama;
2) is able to analyze modern English and American literary works taking into consideration peculiarities of the genre and the author;
3) is able to make research in the area of literature and conduct analysis of a literary text in the volume of bachelor's and master's theses on literature topics.

learning_outcomes.et:
1) on teadlik tänapäeva kirjanduse, ilukirjanduse elementide, luule ja näitekirjanduse teooriatest;
2) on võimeline analüüsima tänapäeva inglise ja ameerika kirjanduse teoseid arvestades žanri ja autori eripärasusi;
3) on võimeline tegema kirjanduslikku teadustööd ning läbi viima kirjandusteksti analüüsi kirjanduslikel teemadel bakalaureuse- ja magistritööde teksti analüüsi mahus.

description.et:
Term tests on literary analysis of fiction, poetry and drama 
A-	analysis of the text is done according to the analysis plan, all questions are answered with maximum precision and reference to corresponding theoretical sources; the answer demonstrates a very high level of independent and creative thinking  and contributes to well-known interpretations of the text.
B-	Analysis follows the plan; all questions are answered correctly and demonstrate very good knowledge of theoretical aspects; the answers reveal the ability of critical thinking and creativity at a very good level; it shows the knowledge of literary critics' opinions of the text. 
C-	Analysis  follows the analysis plan in general, all questions are answered with various degrees of  precision and demonstrate good knowledge of theoretical aspects; the answers  reveal partial readiness of the student to analyse a piece of literature critically; the analysis shows good level of independent thinking.
D-	Analysis answers some research questions and shows  student's  satisfactory knowledge of some theoretical sources to support the analysis; there are some references to other critics' opinions; the analysis demonstrates satisfactory level of  independent thinking and creativity;
E-	Analysis demonstrates student's knowledge of some basic principles of literary analysis and his/her  ability to apply them while analysisng a piece of literature in a conventional way;  the analysis demonstrates a poor  level of  independent thinking and creativity;

Home work assignments 
A-	the paper is presented on time; all tasks are completed in full with excellent  knowledge of background resources and  principles of literary analysis; it demonstrates  creative and independent thinking 
B-	the paper is presented on time; all tasks are completed with very good knowledge of background resources and  principles of literary analysis; it shows very good  ability of the student to apply theoretical knowledge in practice;
C-	the paper is presented on time; all tasks are completed with good knowledge of background resources and  principles of literary analysis; it shows good  ability of the student to apply theoretical knowledge in practice but lacks original thinking; 
D-	the paper is presented with delay; all tasks are completed with satisfactory  knowledge of background resources and  principles of literary analysis
E-	the paper is presented with delay; tasks are completed with satisfactory to poor  knowledge of background resources and  principles of literary analysis.
